{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00205696404/1930112501/0080.xml":{"full_text":"16\nPATRIOT GROUP\nSNIITES LEAGUE\nThe American coalition of\npatriotic societies, made up of\nso|o 67 leading organizations of\nthe\u00bbcountry, was on record today\nin opposition to American ad\nherence to the League Court and\nLeague of Nations and other for\neign entanglements.\nIn a series of resolutions\n'adopted after an all-day meeting\nyesterday, action was taken on\nthese and other questions affecf\ning the country.\nThe coalition urged enactment\nOs laws by Congress to give the\nPresident the right to deport\naliens who in his judgment weie\na \u201cmenace\u201d to American institu\ntions; urged stricter laws govern\ning regulation and deportation of\naliens and the exclusion of un\ndesirables, and as a permanent\npolicy favored cutting in half the\npresent immigrant quotas.\nThe proposal of Senator Reed\n(R.) of Pennsylvania, that all\nimmigration be suspended for\ntwo years, also was endorsed as\nan aid to employment.\nAid Finds Increased\nDemands by Reamers\nMo.e t \u2019.an t.. .o a: mmv tran\nsients have applied for aid from\nthe Washington Travelers\nSociety during the first 10 months\nof 1930 as during all of last year,\nofficials of that organization said\ntoday.\nFollowing a national survey just\ncompleted by the organization, J.\nRogers Flannery, national presi\ndent, has issued an appeal for the\nunemployed to stay at home and\nnot start traveling looking for\nwork.\nNEW RELIEF URGED\nThe Army and Navy Union to\nday urged the President to re\nlieve the business depression and\nhelp the unemployed by cashing\nthe soldiers bonus certificates at\nthis time.\nHOW /WSH\nare YOU going \u2019VHnMBU\nto COOK\nMMI YOUR\n\u25a0HI TURKEY\n\nHere is Miss Turner's\nRFriDP. \u201cMatchless Service will play\nan i m p Or tant part in many\nRfiACT Ti Pkcv Thanksgiving dinners. Its con-\nO ST TLKKEY venience, economy and cleanh-\nWash and prepare a turk